Charles Parsons may refer to: Charles Algernon Parsons (1854–1931), Irish engineer (of Anglo-Irish background) known for his invention of the steam turbine Charles Parsons (philosopher) (born 1933), professor in the philosophy of mathematics at Harvard University Chick Parsons (Charles Thomas Parsons, Jr., 1900–1988), American businessman, diplomat, and decorated World War II veteran Chuck Parsons (Charles W. Parsons, 1924–1999), American sports car racing driver Charlie Parsons (born 1958), television producer Charlie Parsons (baseball) (1863–1936), Major League Baseball pitcher Charles Parsons (company), a large Australian textile company   == See also == Charlie Parsons (disambiguation)
